<aui-inline-dialog id="sp_metadata_dialog" style="max-width:400px">
    <h3>Service Provider Information</h3>
    <hr>
    <p>Provide the metadata information given here to your Identity Provider to enable Bamboo as a service provider.</p>
    <br>
</aui-inline-dialog>

<aui-inline-dialog id="idps_dialog" style="max-width:400px">
    <h3>Configured IDPs</h3>
    <hr>
    <p>View all the configured IDPs on this page. Use the Add New IDP button to start configuring a new IDP.</p>
    <br>
</aui-inline-dialog>

<aui-inline-dialog id="actions_dialog" style="max-width:400px" alignment="top center">
    <h3>Configured IDPs and Actions</h3>
    <hr>
    <p>View, edit, test or delete an IDP from here. You can also enable/disable SSO for Bamboo.</p>
    <br>
</aui-inline-dialog>

<aui-inline-dialog id="idps_overview_dialog" style="max-width:400px">
    <h3>IDP Overview</h3>
    <hr>
    <p>This page shows all the IDP Configurations, User Profile settings and User Groups settings that you have configured.</p>
    <br>
</aui-inline-dialog>
<aui-inline-dialog id="idps_config_dialog" style="max-width:400px">
    <h3>IDP Configurations</h3>
    <hr>
    <p>All the IDP endpoints related settings can be viewed on this page. You can do the IDP configuration manually or
        directly import the IDP metadata using URL or File</p>
    <br>
</aui-inline-dialog>
<aui-inline-dialog id="idps_profile_dialog" style="max-width:400px">
    <h3>User Profile Attribute Mapping</h3>
    <hr>
    <p>This tab provide options to map User profile attributes from IDP to Bamboo attributes so that user details are
        updated in Bamboo at every user login.</p>
    <br>
</aui-inline-dialog>

<aui-inline-dialog id="idps_group_dialog" style="max-width:400px">
    <h3>User Group Mapping</h3>
    <hr>
    <p>Select groups to be assigned to users when they login into Bamboo</p>
    <br>
</aui-inline-dialog>

<aui-inline-dialog id="signin_settings_dialog" style="max-width:400px">
    <h3>Sign In Settings</h3>
    <hr>
    <p>This tab provides an option to force the SSO to users. You can also bypass SSO for some users.(For eg: admins)</p>
    <br>
</aui-inline-dialog>

<aui-inline-dialog id="redirection_rules_dialog" style="max-width:400px">
    <h3>Redirection Rules</h3>
    <hr>
    <p>Now configure rules to apply to your users for SSO based on their domains, groups or directory.</p>
    <br>
</aui-inline-dialog>

<aui-inline-dialog id="look_and_feel_dialog" style="max-width:400px">
    <h3>Custom Login and Error templates</h3>
    <hr>
    <p>Change the look and feel of login page and error pages here.</p>
    <br>
</aui-inline-dialog>

<aui-inline-dialog id="global_sso_settings_dialog" style="max-width:400px">
    <h3>Global Settings</h3>
    <hr>
    <p>Enable/disable complete SSO, auto activate users on SSO and other global settings.</p>
    <br>
</aui-inline-dialog>

<aui-inline-dialog id="backup_and_restore_dialog" style="max-width:400px">
    <h3>Import/Export Plugin Configurations</h3>
    <hr>
    <p>Import plugin file to set this up from existing configuration. Export to take a backup or setup another instance.</p>
    <br>
</aui-inline-dialog>

<aui-inline-dialog id="support_div_dialog" style="max-width:400px">
    <h3>We Are Here!</h3>
    <hr>
    <p>You can reach out to us from here. Our technical team is available to help you with the setup,
        solve your issues and answer you queries.</p>
    <br>
</aui-inline-dialog>
